Interface Generator<T>

Type Parameters:
T - input-type for generator (that can also be iterated over)
All Superinterfaces:
ElementWriter<T>
All Known Subinterfaces:
MultipleFileTypeGenerator<T>, TransformingGenerator<T,​S>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AnnotationAggregateCSVGenerator, AssignmentGenerator, CollectionGenerator, CombinedListGenerator, CSVGenerator, FeatureListCSVGeneratorHorizontal, FeatureListCSVGeneratorVertical, FeatureTableCSVGenerator, GeneratorBridge, KeyValueParamsGenerator, ManifestGenerator, MarksAsUniqueValueGenerator, MarksFlattenedGenerator, MarksGenerator, MarksGeneratorBase, ObjectOutputStreamGenerator, OneStageGenerator, RasterGenerator, RasterGeneratorSelectFormat, SerializedGenerator, SingleFileTypeGenerator, SingleFileTypeGeneratorBridge, StringGenerator, TransformingGeneratorBridge, XMLGenerator, XStreamGenerator
public interface Generator<T>
extends ElementWriter<T>
A class that writes a particular type of object(s) to the filesystem.

The objects to be written are always a function only of the current element.
